      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOLLON (5) doesn't win out of turn and has been 18 months since a success but won't get a better chance to break through. Fitter for two runs back and aided by the extra ground now. Take catching. RHESUS (2) has been going well without winning. Doesn't often race this trip but has placed two of four. Can sit close and should feature. PRINCE RUBAN (1) was a winner here three back then disappointing in the last two. Extra trip looks to suit and in a weak race gets a chance to improve.  DANGER MAN (7) was safely held fresh but will strip far fitter and this suits. Can improve sharply. STRAYA PRIDE (6) was poor at the latest but gave a big sight the start prior and can atone.",
